《'''Turn It Up'''》（台譯：希望盛開）是英國女歌手[[皮克西·洛特|皮克西·洛特]]的第一張個人專輯，於2009年9月14日在英國發行。英國[[iTunes|iTunes]]獨售版本則於2009年12月21日發行，其中新增琵希翻唱[[里昂王族|里昂王族]]熱門單曲《Use Somebody》等六首新歌。專輯發售首週即進入[[英國專輯排行榜|英國專輯排行榜]]第六名，隔週降到第13名，第三週則落到23名。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chartstats.com/albuminfo.php?id=14431 |title=Chart Stats – Pixie Lott – Turn It Up |work=''[[The_Official_Charts_Company|The Official Charts Company]]'' |publisher=Chart Stats |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091129174603/http://www.chartstats.com/albuminfo.php?id=14431 |archivedate=2009年11月29日 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 專輯首波二首主打曲〈媽媽會怎樣〉和〈男孩與女孩〉皆拿下了[[英國單曲排行榜|英國單曲排行榜]]冠軍，而之後的三首發行單曲也都有進入前20名。本專輯在英國本土銷售量達500,000碟，<ref name="The Sun">{{cite web |url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/bizarre/2920296/Pixie-album-to-be-reworked-for-US-market.html |title=A Lott of work to do |work=[[The_Sun_(newspaper)|The Sun]] |publisher=[[News_International|News Group Newspapers Ltd]] |date=5 April 2010 |accessdate=12 April 2010 |quote=They are concerned that Turn It Up has only sold about half a million copies. |archive-date=2013-12-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131209044743/http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/bizarre/2920296/Pixie-album-to-be-reworked-for-US-market.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 並於2010年1月25日獲得英國唱片產業協會白金級唱片認證。

本專輯於2010年10月18日以"''Turn It Up Louder''"之名改版重製發行。新改版專輯收錄十首新單曲，包含最新主打單曲"Broken Arrow"。<ref>{{cite web |last=Copsey |first=Robert |title=Pixie Lott confirms LP re-release |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a278214/pixie-lott-confirms-lp-re-release.html |publisher=[[Digital_Spy|Digital Spy]] |date=22 September 2010 |accessdate=25 September 2010 |archive-date=2010-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101026212117/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a278214/pixie-lott-confirms-lp-re-release.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="HMV">{{cite web |url=http://hmv.com/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?ctx=280;0;-1;-1;-1&sku=388573 |title=Pixie Lott: Turn It Up Louder (2010): CD |publisher=[[HMV_Group|HMV]] |accessdate=18 September 2010 |archive-date=2010-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101126134145/http://hmv.com/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?ctx=280%3B0%3B-1%3B-1%3B-1&sku=388573 |dead-url=no }}</ref> "''Turn It Up Louder''"專輯當中收錄了一首與 [[傑森·德魯羅|傑森·德魯羅]]共同錄製的單曲名為"Coming Home"。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://hmv.com/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?sku=388573 |title=Turn It Up Louder @ HMV |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archive-date=2010-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101022052133/http://hmv.com/hmvweb/displayProductDetails.do?sku=388573 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sihjKQOAL3M |title='Coming Home' featuring Jason Derulo - Official YouTube Clip |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archive-date=2019-02-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218054028/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sihjKQOAL3M |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==評價==
Metacritic給予本專輯44/100分，顯示本專輯評價貶大於褒。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/artists/lottpixie/turnitup |title=Turn It Up reviews at Metacritic.com |work=''[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]'' |publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive Inc]] |accessdate=8 May 2010 |archive-date=2010-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100328142514/http://www.metacritic.com/music/artists/lottpixie/turnitup |dead-url=no }}</ref> 有些樂評認為這張專輯缺乏原創性，並認為這是張「 對於充滿潛力的樂壇新生而言或許稱不上經典，但卻十分有派頭的專輯。」[[BBC_Music|BBC Music]]的Paul Leste說道：「《希望盛開》的有些曲子的確聽起來像是出自新興R&B女歌星口中的歌。這是褒也是貶：不論是充滿60年代舞踏風格的〈媽媽會怎樣〉還是如同馬克·羅森般花裏胡哨的〈男孩與女孩〉，這些歌曲聽起來都 沒甚麼個性。」<ref name="bbc">{{cite web |last=Lester |first=Paul |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/r9dp |title=Review of Pixie Lott – Turn It Up |work=''[[BBC_Music|BBC Music]]'' |publisher=[[BBC_Online|BBC Online]] |date=2 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2012-07-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68pOVUbc8?url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/r9dp |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[Allmusic|Allmusic]]》的 [[Stephen_Thomas_Erlewine|Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] 則說：「雖然專輯裡頭不時有活潑的美聲搭襯，琵希高吭的歌聲也足讓人叫好，但這些都不足以讓《希望盛開》順勢回歸這一波由[[艾美·懷絲|艾美·懷絲]]和[[黛菲|黛菲]]領導的靈魂樂潮。琵希本人似乎不希望世人已超齡的眼光看待她…更不用說合聲本身又是如此地充滿現代感。」<ref name="allmusic">{{cite web |last=Erlewine |first=Stephen Thomas |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/turn-it-up-louder-r1630729 |title=Turn It Up > Overview |work=''[[Allmusic|Allmusic]]'' |publisher=[[Rovi_Corporation|Rovi Corporation]] |accessdate=10 December 2009 |archive-date=2011-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110429141100/http://www.allmusic.com/album/turn-it-up-louder-r1630729 }}</ref>《每日星報》的Sarah-Louise Jame則認為：「 在這位[[埃塞克斯|埃塞克斯]]的小女生身上幾乎可看到所有英倫知名歌星的影子：艾美的恢弘低沉、黛菲的風情萬種和甜心寶貝（{{link-en|Sugababes|Sugababes}}）的火熱動感。」<ref name="dailystar">{{cite web |last=James |first=Sarah-Louise |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/music/view/99957/ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK-Pixie-Lott-Turn-It-Up/ |title=Album of the Week – Pixie Lott: Turn It Up |work=[[每日星报|Daily Star]] |publisher=Northern and Shell Media Publications |date=16 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68pOK38W2?url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/music/view/99957/ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK-Pixie-Lott-Turn-It-Up/ |archive-date=2012-07-01 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 《數位間諜》的音樂編輯Nick Levine則認為「《希望盛開》是張惹人憐愛的作品－這都要歸功於這位熱情洋溢的小女生－但總覺得還是少了點驚喜」，並將〈吸引〉〈放膽去做〉〈重新開始〉列為本輯必聽單曲。<ref name="digital">{{cite web |last=Levine |first=Nick |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/a177453/pixie-lott-turn-it-up.html |title=Pixie Lott: 'Turn It Up' |publisher=[[Digital_Spy|Digital Spy]] |date=14 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2009-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091027234355/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/a177453/pixie-lott-turn-it-up.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 《[[星期日泰晤士報|星期日泰晤士報]]》的Dan Cairns則說：「假使這張專輯在三十年前發行的話－除了其中兩首瑕疵品（〈我的至愛〉和〈沒人比得上你〉）之外－肯定會是張出類拔萃而轟動一時的作品，果真如此的話如今它或許還稱得上是再版中的無敵專輯呢。」<ref name="sunday times">{{cite web |last=Cairns |first=Dan |url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/music/cd_reviews/article6827346.ece |title=Pixie Lott: Turn It Up |work=[[The_Sunday_Times|The Sunday Times]] |publisher=[[The_Times|Times Online]] |date=13 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2011-06-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615161429/http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/music/cd_reviews/article6827346.ece |dead-url=no }}</ref> 雅虎音樂的Dan Gennoe則附註：「顯而易見地這張充滿暢銷金曲和王牌製作的專輯打從一開始就一心只想在排行榜上爭奇鬥豔，至於專輯其餘的歌曲，容我這麼說，不外乎是中規中矩的民謠、固守舊規的創作以及一些搖擺其中的產物－也就是用來充數的。 」<ref name="yahoo">{{cite web |last=Gennoe |first=Dan |url=http://uk.launch.yahoo.com/090915/33/221r6.html |title=Pixie Lott – Turn It Up |work=''[[Yahoo!_Music|Yahoo! Music UK]]'' |publisher=[[Yahoo!|Yahoo! Inc]] |date=15 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2011-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613143833/http://uk.launch.yahoo.com/090915/33/221r6.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>《每日快報》的Robert Spellman認為單曲〈媽媽會怎樣〉有著「整張專輯不曾展現的感覺，那是一種貌似性感的自信以及一種想必連[[女神卡卡|女神卡卡]]都會認同的圓滿感，」並認為專輯中「老套的強力情歌（Power ballads）〈為我哭泣〉以及過度成熟的R&B試圖引領琵希－正確而言是編曲者們－誤入歧途；實際上這時候注於表面功夫或許還比較適當。」<ref name="daily_ex">{{cite web |last=Spellman |first=Robert |url=http://www.express.co.uk/entertainment/view/129846 |title=Pixie Lott: Turn It Up |work=[[Daily_Express|Daily Express]] |publisher=Northern and Shell Media Publications |date=25 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2012-06-30 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120630062407/http://www.express.co.uk/entertainment/view/129846 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>《[[每日電訊報|每日電訊報]]》的Helen Brown認為琵希是「活潑而有[[菲絲特|菲絲特]]的感覺，但和當今樂壇的其他流行女歌手沒甚麼兩樣。」<ref name="daily_te">{{cite web |last=Brown |first=Helen |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/cdreviews/6162822/Pixie-Lott-Turn-it-Up-CD-review.html |title=Pixie Lott: Turn it Up, CD review |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=Telegraph Media Group Limited |date=11 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2009-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090914122214/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/cdreviews/6162822/Pixie-Lott-Turn-it-Up-CD-review.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> musicOMH網站的Michael Cragg毫不留情地說：「一張由擁有大嗓門的『才女』用哭聲所作出來的中庸作品。」<ref name="musicomh">{{cite web |last=Cragg |first=Michael |url=http://www.musicomh.com/albums/pixie-lott_0909.htm |title=Pixie Lott – Turn It Up |publisher=[[musicOMH|musicOMH]] |accessdate=8 May 2010 |archive-date=2010-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100301225312/http://www.musicomh.com/albums/pixie-lott_0909.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 《[[觀察家報|觀察家報]]》的Imogen Carter則說：「這張專輯就像[[迪士尼|迪士尼]]的原聲帶一樣充滿老掉牙和似曾相似的歌曲。」<ref name="observer">{{cite web |last=Carter |first=Imogen |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2009/sep/13/pixie-lott-turn-it-up |title=Pixie Lott: Turn it up |work=[[The_Observer|The Observer]] |publisher=[[guardian.co.uk|guardian.co.uk]] |date=13 September 2009 |accessdate=11 October 2009 |archive-date=2009-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091026172407/http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2009/sep/13/pixie-lott-turn-it-up |dead-url=no }}</ref>

